OL,3,CChristian sacked over online posts
OL,4,Csays she is 'not alone' ahead of appeal
OL,6,FAn anonymous complaint was made to the
OL,7,Fschool and Mrs Higgs was suspended
OL,8,Fand, following a disciplinary hearing,
OL,9,Fdismissed for gross misconduct.
OL,11,FMrs Higgs, supported by the Christian
OL,12,FLegal Centre, took the school to an
OL,13,Femployment tribunal, arguing she had
OL,14,Fbeen unlawfully discriminated against
OL,15,Fbecause of her Christian beliefs.
OL,17,FThe school denied dismissing the
OL,18,Fmother-of-two because of her religious
OL,19,Fbeliefs and said she was sacked
OL,20,Fbecause of the language used in the
OL,21,Fposts.
